outdoors during construction. Noise from 
				pile driving is expected to be heard by people who are outdoors 
				up to 1,000 feet from the pile driving location. People within 
				2,000 feet may feel ground vibrations from pile driving.</p>
				<p>Based on the results, the level of vibration from pile 
				driving is not expected to cause any structural damage to nearby 
				buildings or structures, however, windows, dishes or loose items 
				on shelves could rattle during impact hammering during future 
				construction.</p>
